MetaDescription: Connect your WooCommerce store with your CRM, Marketing suite, accounts platform and more, by building your own automation workflows with Cyclr's drag and drop builder.
Content:
Integrate WooCommerce

Connect WooCommerce to many other apps without code

As one of the world’s most popular eCommerce solutions WooCommerce can get your online store up & selling in no time; but how can you integrate it with the rest of your business?

Cyclr gives you the ability to create your own WooCommerce integrations, letting you connect your store to your CRM, Email marketing platform, support service and much more.

Automate admin tasks, refine your marketing, deliver better customer service...all with Cyclr!

Case Studies Pre-made Integrations Features Request a Demo
Case Studies

How Cyclr integrates and automates Twilio

Making the Most of Insightly WooCommerce Integration

You can create a cycle that sends completed orders from WooCommerce to your Insightly account as a new Opportunity. Cyclr’s “Branch” function lets you look at the the data to see if it is already in Insightly, preventing data duplication, adding the order as a completed Opportunity if it isn’t already listed. These new sales leads can be given a custom opportunity sale state to make reporting on your website’s successes even easier!

Email Marketing Integrations


Cyclr support a wide (and growing) range of email marketing suites, that allow you to create beautiful and dynamic email campaigns. Our marketing integrations take a lot of the hassle out of creating more bespoke, user centric campaigns that really speak to your customers, as well as keeping the rest of your team in the loop. Plus, the drag and drop interface means you can set up custom workflows for new campaigns in minutes!

Pre-built WooCommerce integrations

Try any of these WooCommerce integrations, no account required

Automatically update your stocking sheet from WooCommerce product listings

Automatically keep your stocking spreadsheet up to date with this WooCommerce & Google Sheets integration.

Try it now

Creating & Adding Contacts to Mailchimp Segments Based on What the Customer has Bought

This cycle looks at orders made on WooCommerce, first looking at if the orderer's email address is already in the Mailchimp "Customer" list. If not, it adds it. It then looks to see if there is a segment within the list that matches the product sold, if there isn't one it creates one, adding the customer to that segment of the list.

Try it now

Add New WooCommerce Orders as Completed Insightly Opportunity

The WooCommerce order number is compared to the list of Insightly opportunities. If the number doesn't appear in the list a new completed Opportunity is created.

Try it now
